{
  "texts": [
    "The needs extraction system interacts with the LLM to analyze user statements and obtain an overview of the service and the corresponding needs.",
    "The extraction of needs for undeveloped services is conducted in the following three steps:• Step 1-1: Extract candidate services from user utterances; • Step 1-2: Identify the service and needs from from user utterances; • Step 1-3: If the service is unknown, register a new service overview.In this research, a service repository is newly prepared to manage services.",
    "The service repository defines a service (1)I 6 = f (I 2 + I 3 + I 5) = f Δ 1 + Δ � 2 + r 2 Δ � 2 Δ 4 I 1 where Δ � 2 = Δ 1 Δ 3 + Δ 2data model with at least the following three elements and provides functions for registering and retrieving these services:• service_name: Service name;• description: Service overview;• is_released: Development flag (developed or undeveloped).Step 1-1 extracts all words from the user's statements that are presumed to represent service names.",
    "This is because service names encapsulate the core concept of the service.In the next step, Step 1-2, these candidates will be refined to narrow down the service intended by the user.",
    "While prior research relied on string searches of registered service names, making it impossible to target undeveloped new services, this study achieves the extraction of unregistered services by automatically generating new service names based on the content of the user's statements."
  ]
}